<entry code="DQC.US.0117.10093" level="error">
 <message filing_url="http://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1939365/000121390024052574/ea0207710-s1_inspire.htm" severity="error" effectiveDate="2023-08-31" cid="2184246866192">[DQC.US.0117.10093] In the statement 001 - Statement - Unaudited Condensed Consolidated Balance Sheets the concept us-gaap:CommonStockValue with a value of 7 and dimension of us-gaap:StatementClassOfStockAxis and member of us-gaap:CommonClassAMember is not equal to the dimensional breakdown of 705 using the dimension us-gaap:StatementClassOfStockAxis and the second dimension srt:RestatementAxis:
	CommonClassAMember 	 --> 705 	 --> srt:RestatementAxis=srt:ScenarioPreviouslyReportedMember, us-gaap:StatementClassOfStockAxis=us-gaap:CommonClassAMember 


On the face financial statements it is expected that values reported are dimensionally complete for a given line item. If you added up the values of the dimensions the resulting sum should represent the actual aggregate value.  This rule takes the dimensional values of an axis reported on the face financial statements and adds them up and compares them to the actual aggregate value reported anywhere in the filing. If they are different the rule reports an error.

The properties of this us-gaap:CommonStockValue fact are:
Period :2023-12-31
Unit : USD
Dimensions : us-gaap:StatementClassOfStockAxis=us-gaap:CommonClassAMember
Rule Element Id:10093
